##### Bordered Table

Create a responsive table by wrapping your table inside a <div> element with a .overflow-x-scroll class or, 
if you want your table to act responsive only when viewed on a mobile device add the 
.mobile-overflow-x-scroll instead. You must also add a .responsive class to your table element. 

##### html
----------

```
<!-- Responsive Div Wrapper Start -->
<div class="overflow-x-scroll mobile-overflow-x-scroll">
<table class="responsiv">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>...</th>
      <th>...</th>
      <th>...</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>...</td>
      <td>...</td>
      <td>...</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
<!-- Responsive Div Wrapper End -->
```

### Custom Table

Let's see in few code examples how you can create a custom table using core modules such as colors.css and modifier.css.

By adding .border-*color class modifier to our bordered table we can change the border color of our table. 
By adding .border-*width class modifier to our bordered table we can change the border width of our table. 
*width can be from 2 up to 6;

##### html
----------

```
<table class="bordered border-blue border-2">...</table>
```

In example below we've added an extra class .text-strong to our <table> element to make table text thicker. 
We've also added .fill-blue and .text-white to our <thead> element to add a blue background with white text.

##### html
----------

```
<table class="bordered border-blue border-2 text-strong">
  <thead class="fill-blue text-white">
    <tr>
      <th>...</th>
      <th>...</th>
      <th>...</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>...</td>
      <td>...</td>
      <td>...</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
```

